.TH MKDIR(1),User Commands,MKDIR(1)

.SH NAME
mkdir - create directories

.SH SYNOPSIS
mkdir directory ...

.SH DESCRIPTION
mkdir creates each named directory.
At least one operand is required.

A single trailing slash on any operand is stripped before the directory is created.

mkdir does not create intermediate parent directories; every component up to the final name must already exist.

.SH DIAGNOSTICS
mkdir: missing operand - no arguments were given.

Error creating directory 'X' - the directory could not be created (already exists, parent missing, filesystem error, etc.).
mkdir continues with any remaining operands after reporting the error.

.SH EXIT STATUS
0: All directories created successfully.

1: No operand was given, or at least one directory failed to be created.
